{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-project-jsx","path":"/projects/git-art/","result":{"data":{"post":{"html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 750px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/8f020bc41428522db3e5eb6a932a4ea9/d438d/git-art.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 81.91489361702128%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Git Art\"\n        title=\"Git Art\"\n        src=\"/static/8f020bc41428522db3e5eb6a932a4ea9/1d69c/git-art.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/8f020bc41428522db3e5eb6a932a4ea9/4dcb9/git-art.png 188w,\n/static/8f020bc41428522db3e5eb6a932a4ea9/5ff7e/git-art.png 375w,\n/static/8f020bc41428522db3e5eb6a932a4ea9/1d69c/git-art.png 750w,\n/static/8f020bc41428522db3e5eb6a932a4ea9/78797/git-art.png 1125w,\n/static/8f020bc41428522db3e5eb6a932a4ea9/aa440/git-art.png 1500w,\n/static/8f020bc41428522db3e5eb6a932a4ea9/d438d/git-art.png 2290w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>My roommate <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/timothylee0/\" title=\"Tim\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">Tim</a> and I decided to start challenging ourselves with little applications we could develop.</p>\n<p>The first thing we thought of was a way to decorate your GitHub activity board, example below:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 750px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/95fe588730f42523bf7f534245c5a07b/d74fe/example-board.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 21.808510638297875%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Example board\"\n        title=\"Example board\"\n        src=\"/static/95fe588730f42523bf7f534245c5a07b/1d69c/example-board.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/95fe588730f42523bf7f534245c5a07b/4dcb9/example-board.png 188w,\n/static/95fe588730f42523bf7f534245c5a07b/5ff7e/example-board.png 375w,\n/static/95fe588730f42523bf7f534245c5a07b/1d69c/example-board.png 750w,\n/static/95fe588730f42523bf7f534245c5a07b/78797/example-board.png 1125w,\n/static/95fe588730f42523bf7f534245c5a07b/d74fe/example-board.png 1164w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>The idea being that you could just draw or type (or both) anything that you wanted to on a canvas that represented your github activity board, and with one simple script you could create the required commits and upload that new repo to your GitHub.</p>\n<p>We used React for the front end, and wrote simple JavaScript functions to generate the bash script which is available for you to download and run.</p>\n<p>Made open source under the <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"http://www.wtfpl.net\" title=\"WTFPL licence\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">WTFPL licence</a>.</p>","excerpt":"My roommate  and I decided to start challenging ourselves with little applications we could develop. The first thing we thought of was a way to decorate your GitHub activity board, example below:  The…","frontmatter":{"title":"🖌 Git Art","date":"February, 2019","tech":["Javascript","React","Bash"],"link":"https://jamesjarvis.github.io/git-art/","source":"https://github.com/jamesjarvis/git-art","previewImage":{"childImageSharp":{"resize":{"src":"/static/8f020bc41428522db3e5eb6a932a4ea9/f3583/git-art.png","height":983,"width":1200}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/projects/git-art/"}}}